# Value capture requires parallel progress on technology and organization
@type: two_column

@col:
  ## Technology Foundation
  - Unified data layer with governed model access
  - Model selection framework (build vs. buy vs. fine-tune)
  - MLOps platform for deployment and monitoring
  - API gateway for enterprise-wide model serving

@col:
  ## Organizational Enablement
  - AI fluency training for 100% of knowledge workers
  - Dedicated AI product management function
  - Talent pipeline: ML engineers, data scientists, AI PMs
  - Change management and adoption playbooks

@notes: Technology without org enablement consistently fails. Org readiness without technology investment is wasted preparation. Both must advance in lockstep.

---

# Eighteen-month path from isolated pilots to enterprise deployment
@type: timeline

@step: Months 1–3 | Foundation | Data audit, use case prioritization, talent assessment, governance
@step: Months 4–6 | Pilot | 3–5 high-value use cases, model deployment, KPI baseline
@step: Months 7–12 | Scale | Expand proven use cases, AI platform build, Center of Excellence
@step: Months 13–18 | Embed | Enterprise-wide rollout, self-serve AI tooling, value tracking

@source: BCG AI Transformation Methodology, 2024

@notes: Clients reliably want to skip foundation. Hold the line — bad data and unclear use cases kill every scaling effort.

